&lt;p>Father of two, I don&amp;rsquo;t have as much hobby time as I once did, but, like yielding choice to a radio DJ, it has been a great forcing function to venture into new territory. I&amp;rsquo;ve written apps to support my son&amp;rsquo;s &lt;a href="https://print-proxy-cards.robmeyer.net">Pokémon obsession&lt;/a> and &lt;a href="https://arrow-maze-creator.robmeyer.net">generate arrow mazes&lt;/a> to keep him busy. These toy projects are an opportunity to toy with a new [to me at least] technology (e.g. solidjs) or deepen my understanding of a familiar technology (e.g. optimizing css for print media) along the way.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Cyclist</title><link>https://robmeyer.net/cyclist/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://robmeyer.net/cyclist/</guid><description>&lt;iframe height='900' frameborder='0' allowtransparency='true' scrolling='no' src='https://www.strava.com/athletes/6106508/latest-rides/c56b273262b6a22ff5d82a687f7aff462ca21c7a'>&lt;/iframe></description></item><item><title>Maker</title><link>https://robmeyer.net/maker/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://robmeyer.net/maker/</guid><description>&lt;a data-pin-do="embedBoard" data-pin-board-width="700" data-pin-scale-height="750" data-pin-scale-width="300" href="https://www.pinterest.com/robizzle01/made-by-rob-meyer/">&lt;/a>
